'''Muhammad ibn Abi Bakr al-Farisi''' (d. 1278/1279), an [[Iranian people|Iranian]]<ref>[http://www.fulviofrisone.com/attachments/article/464/Springer-Verlag%20The%20Biographical%20Encyclopedia%20of%20Astronomers.pdf/ The Biographical Encyclopedia of Astronomers] : page 10 : "He was a contemporary of the ruler Ashraf and Muḥammad ibn Abī Bakr al-Fārisī, the latter also of Iranian stock."</ref> [[Islamic astronomer]] and [[Islamic astrology|astrologer]] born in [[Aden]]. He is the author of ''al-Tuḥfa'', which includes a treatise containing important information for the history of Islamic astronomy and its connection with the religion of [[Islam]].{{sfn|Schmidl|2007}} 

